              â€¢ Personal projects where design doesn't matter<br>
              â€¢ Students who need something up for a class<br>
              â€¢ Non-profits with zero budget
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-yellow-900 mt-2">
              <strong>Who is it NOT for?</strong> Anyone who cares about design, brand identity, or professionalism. Spend $15/month on Framer instead.
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            I rated Hostinger 7.8/10. The score would be lower if not for the price. If Hostinger cost $15/month? It'd be a 5/10.
          </p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            But at $2.99? It earns points just for existing. Sometimes "cheap and functional" is exactly what you need.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- When Hostinger Failed Me -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 to-gray-800 border-[3px] border-green-500 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white mb-2">The Hostinger Trade-off: When $2.99 Cost Me Clients</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Cheap upfront, expensive later</p>

