              "Hostinger is $2.99/month!" Only with a 48-month contract ($144 upfront). Client wanted month-to-month: $7.99/mo. "That's still cheap," they said. Six months later: "We need more storage, more email accounts, better performance." Now they're on the $12.99/mo plan. That's more expensive than Framer ($15/mo) with worse features. The "cheap" option became expensive.
            </p>
